CSS used to style HTML documents 
x.css files store all styles in separate file than the html document
  - link element
    - <link rel="stylesheet" href="styles.css">

/* comment */

Elements 
  style : sepcify properties for elements
    - element1, element2, element3... { property: value; }
    - properties
      - text-align: center...
      - background-color: color
      - border-color: color
      - border-left/right/top/bottom-width: 10px
      - background-image: imageURL
      - font-family: font, fallback_font
      - font-size: 30px
      - width: 100px or x%
      - max-width: 500px
      - margin-left/right: auto 
        - center horizontally by setting left and right margin to auto
      - padding-left/right/top/bottom: 20px
        - padding: 20px would do all 4 properties
      - display: inline-block
      - color
      
  div : design layout purposes 
    - used inside body
    - id="name"
    - class="name"

  article : contains multiple elements that have related information
  hr : divider
    - self closing
    - height property

For styling of the page to look similar on mobile and desktop add thsi meta element with content attribute in the head: 
  - <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

#id selector targest elements with id attribute
.class selector 
  - class attribute can be applied to any element
  - .class element { } styles all of that element in the class
pseudo selector for when link is visited
  - a:visisted { property: value }
  - a:hover { property: value } 
  - a:active { property: value }
